Function Reference/wp delete post revision « WordPress Codex
-----------

Deletes a revision.

Deletes the row from the posts table corresponding to the specified
revision.

Usage
-----

` <?php wp_delete_post_revision( $revision_id ); ?> `

Parameters
----------

 `$revision_id` 
:   ([*int|object*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Int.7Cobject "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) Revision ID or revision object.
    Default: *None*

Return Values
-------------

 `` `(mixed)`{style="color:gray"} 
:   Null or WP\_Error if error, deleted post if success.

Change Log
----------

Since: [2.6](/Version_2.6 "Version 2.6")

Source File
-----------

`wp_delete_post_revision()` is located in `wp-includes/post.php`

